extends /views/templates/layouts/_base

append variables
	- pagetitle = "Persisting state"

block content
	.lane
		.container
			.page-header
				h1 Persisting state
				p.lead Remember states across page loads.

	+section("How it works")
		p Both components determine the initial state on every page load from these sources, checked in order:
		.card
			ol
				li #[strong URL param] (#[code ?panel=]): Reading of the URL parameter will always be done, no config needed. See #[a(href="/sharedconcepts/deep-linking.html") Deep linking].
				li #[strong localStorage]: used when #[code persist] is enabled and no URL param applied. See below.
				li #[strong HTML default]: the markup state like #[code class="active"] panel (PanelSet) or #[code class="is-open"] (Panel / closable PanelSet).

		p #[strong localStorage is only read when you opt in] via #[code persist]. A component without it always uses the URL param or its HTML default, so a stored entry from another page can never reopen it unexpectedly.

		p On this page we delve a bit deeper into #[strong persisting state].


	+section("Reading localStorage")
		p #[strong Reading is opt-in.] localStorage is only checked on load when the component has #[code persist] enabled. Without it, the stored value is ignored and the HTML default is used.

		p State is stored under keys scoped to the current page path, so auto-assigned ids (#[code panel-1], #[code panel-2], …) on different pages never collide:
		.card
			table.table
				thead
					tr
						th Component
						th Key format
						th Example (on #[code /docs/tabs])
				tbody
					tr
						td PanelSet
						td #[code &lt;pathname&gt;::ps:&lt;container-id&gt;]
						td #[code /docs/tabs::ps:main-tabs]
					tr
						td Panel
						td #[code &lt;pathname&gt;::panel:&lt;element-id&gt;]
						td #[code /docs/tabs::panel:sidebar]

			p The #[code &lt;pathname&gt;] prefix is #[code location.pathname], added automatically. You don’t set it. It just keeps each page’s state separate.


	+section("Writing localStorage")

		p #[strong Writing is optional.] Enable #[code persist] to save panel state to localStorage whenever a panel opens or closes. On the next load, the stored state is restored automatically.

		.card
			.grid-2

				div
					h3 Persist in Panel
					.demo
						button(aria-controls="panelpersist" aria-expanded="false") Toggle panel

						div#panelpersist(data-panel data-panel-persist)
							.panel-wrapper
								h3= example1Title
								+example-1-content

					div.bottom.column.gap-1
						+codeblock('JavaScript').
							new Panel('#sidebar', { persist: true });
							// or via init
							Panel.init({ persist: true });

						+codeblock('HTML')
							#sidebar(data-panel data-panel-persist) ...

				div
					h3 Persist in PanelSet
					.demo
						+exampletabset('panelsetpersist')
						+examplepanelset('panelsetpersist')(data-panel-persist)

					div.bottom.column.gap-1
						+codeblock('JavaScript').
							new PanelSet('#tabs', { persist: true });
							// or via init
							PanelSet.init({ persist: true });

						+codeblock('HTML')
							#tabs(data-panelset data-panel-persist) ...

			p Play around with the two examples above, and reload the page. Both come back in the same state you left them.

		p For accordion groups, set #[code data-panel-persist] on the #[code [data-panel-group]] element to cover all panels in the group at once.

	+section("Global persist and opting out")
		p #[code init({ persist: true })] turns persistence on for every matching component. Two things keep that from being heavy-handed:

		.card
			ul
				li #[strong An #[code id] is required to store anything.] A PanelSet writes under its container #[code id]; a Panel under its element #[code id]. A component without an #[code id] silently persists nothing, so a global flag only saves the components you’ve deliberately identified.
				li #[strong Any component can opt out.] A per-element #[code data-panel-persist="false"] overrides the global option (attributes are the most specific setting). Inside a persisting #[code [data-panel-group]], a panel’s own #[code data-panel-persist="false"] also wins over the group.

		+codeblock('HTML')
			// Persists: inherits init({ persist: true }) and has an id
			#saved(data-panelset)
				.panel-wrapper ...
			+n
			// Never persists: no id to key on
			div(data-panelset)
				.panel-wrapper ...
			+n
			// Opts out explicitly, even under a global persist
			#opted-out(data-panelset data-panel-persist="false")
				.panel-wrapper ...


append scripts
	if isProd
		script(src=`${basePath}assets/scripts/example.js` vite-ignore)
		script(src=`${basePath}lib/panelset.js` vite-ignore)
		script.
			Panel.init();
			PanelSet.init();
	else
		script(type="module" src="/src/assets/scripts/example.js")
		script(type="module").
			import { PanelSet, Panel } from 'panelset';
			Panel.init({ debug: true });
			PanelSet.init({ debug: true });
